The "accuracy" metric is linked to "machine learning" and "descriptive" entities, but not directly to DRI Corpus or its models.

Given the structure of the ORKG data, it seems that evaluation metrics are not directly linked to the DRI Corpus dataset or its models in a straightforward way. However, based on the information retrieved:
- The DRI Corpus is used for classification tasks.
- The only model explicitly linked is Linear SVM.
- The most common evaluation metrics for classification tasks (and likely for DRI Corpus) are accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score.

To provide a comprehensive answer, I will write a SPARQL query that retrieves all metrics (entities of type Metric) that are used in the context of the DRI Corpus dataset, either directly or via associated models or contributions, if such links exist.

Here is the query:

```sparql
SELECT DISTINCT ?metric ?metricLabel WHERE {
  {
    # Metrics directly linked to DRI Corpus
    <http://orkg.org/orkg/resource/R209701> ?p ?metric .
    ?metric a <http://orkg.org/orkg/class/Metric> .
    OPTIONAL { ?metric rdfs:label ?metricLabel }
  }
  UNION
  {
    # Metrics linked via models
    <http://orkg.org/orkg/resource/R209701> orkgp:P1004 ?model .
    ?model ?p2 ?metric .
    ?metric a <http://orkg.org/orkg/class/Metric> .
    OPTIONAL { ?metric rdfs:label ?metricLabel }
  }
  UNION
  {
    # Metrics linked via contributions mentioning DRI Corpus
    ?contrib ?p3 <http://orkg.org/orkg/resource/R209701> .
    ?contrib ?p4 ?metric .
    ?metric a <http://orkg.org/orkg/class/Metric> .
    OPTIONAL { ?metric rdfs:label ?metricLabel }
  }
}
```

This query will return all metrics (with their IRIs and optional labels) that are associated with the DRI Corpus dataset, either directly, via models, or via contributions.

