messages.content:
Listing all evaluations for all entities is too broad and not efficient. Since the only evaluation found directly linked to the AG News benchmark is "Evaluation Error_4.45" using the "Error" metric, it appears that "Error" is the only metric currently associated with model evaluation on the AG News benchmark in ORKG.

Now, I will write a SPARQL query that finds all metrics used in evaluations associated with the AG News benchmark dataset (including both the dataset and benchmark entities, to be thorough).

Here is the query:

```sparql
SELECT DISTINCT ?metric ?metricLabel WHERE {
  VALUES ?agnews { 
    <http://orkg.org/orkg/resource/R116787>  # AG News Dataset
    <http://orkg.org/orkg/resource/R130150>  # Benchmark AG News
  }
  ?agnews orkgp:HAS_EVALUATION ?evaluation .
  ?evaluation orkgp:HAS_METRIC ?metric .
  OPTIONAL { ?metric rdfs:label ?metricLabel }
}
```

This will return all metrics (and their labels, if available) used to evaluate models on the AG News benchmark dataset in ORKG.

