messages.content:
Thank you for the feedback. To refine the query for better usability, I will add OPTIONAL clauses to retrieve human-readable labels for the contribution, benchmark, and paper entities, while still ensuring that the actual IRIs are returned. This will make the results more understandable without sacrificing completeness.

Here is the improved SPARQL query:

SELECT ?contribution ?contributionLabel ?code_link ?benchmark ?benchmarkLabel ?paper ?paperLabel WHERE {
  ?contribution orkgp:HAS_MODEL <http://orkg.org/orkg/resource/R124891> .
  ?contribution orkgp:HAS_BENCHMARK ?benchmark .
  ?contribution orkgp:HAS_SOURCE_CODE ?code_link .
  OPTIONAL { ?paper orkgp:hasContribution ?contribution . }
  OPTIONAL { ?contribution rdfs:label ?contributionLabel . }
  OPTIONAL { ?benchmark rdfs:label ?benchmarkLabel . }
  OPTIONAL { ?paper rdfs:label ?paperLabel . }
}

This query will return the IRIs and, where available, the labels for contributions, benchmarks, and papers, along with the code links.

Now, I will submit this refined query as the answer.

function.arguments:
{"kg":"orkg","sparql":"SELECT ?contribution ?contributionLabel ?code_link ?benchmark ?benchmarkLabel ?paper ?paperLabel WHERE {
  ?contribution orkgp:HAS_MODEL <http://orkg.org/orkg/resource/R124891> .
